<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>4-211.05</num>
  <heading>Authorization of payment for moving costs.</heading>
  <text>The payment may be authorized:</text>
  <para>
    <num>(1)</num>
    <text>As a money payment to the recipient when he or she makes his or her own arrangements for moving; or</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(2)</num>
    <text>As a vendor payment to the moving firm when arrangements must be made by the Mayor.</text>
  </para>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 4-101" type="History" path="§1105">Apr. 6, 1982, D.C. Law 4-101, § 1105, 29 DCR 1060</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1981 Ed., § 3-211.5.</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>
